betterquesting:10.desc:8:
You were going for a walk in the park and all of a sudden the apocalypse happened. The sky turned crimson and the land aroound you disappeared into the endless void. You were left on a small island with no obvious resources.

 The Grass below you seemed hard, so you started digging through it (via shift+right-clicking). You found some Pebbles in it and used them to make Cobblestone. You kept digging and digging and it seemed like there was an infinite amount of Pebbles.

You saw that there are some Roots sticking out of your island. Maybe you could use them for creating Saplings.

 You did that and planted the Sapling. It seemed to slightly grow when you were.... twerking near it? However, there was something in the sky that was stopping it from growing, so you broke it.
The tools made in a Crafting Table only get so good. Using a few different "Tables" you might be able to create much more useful tools.
You are going to need Bones for Bone Meal and Rotten Flesh for proteins, so you should build a mob farm.
So you decided to grow the Grass around you. Upon breaking, some of it dropped Seeds. You thought you could make a small farm with them, so you planted them on Crop Sticks.

The Petals of the Mystical Flowers you made seemed to attract each other and started to form new Flowers, but they couldn't quite do it on their own. So, you made an Apothecary and, using a Bowl, you filled it up with Water. Now, let's see what happens if you throw them in it, together with a few Seeds.

You have noticed that when crushing down Crystals, a part of them becomes a fluid. Now that you have Seared Bricks, you could make a Table and Basin for casting said fluid into Ingots, Nuggets and Blocks.
Using White Petals, you've created the purest of Daisies. It seems to have some magical properties as it can transmute certain blocks around it.
With a few Red, Brown and Light Gray Petals, you've managed to create a flower that uses fuel to generate a form of mystical energy, Mana.

With Livingwood and Livingrock, you seem to be able to manipulate mana, so you made a Mana Spreader for transferring it and a Mana Pool for capturing it. It seems that certain items can absorb the mana from the Pool.
Gravel is essentially Sand with a few impurities, meaning that you should be able to just put it on a Crushing Table and wack it with a Stone Hammer to turn it into Sand.

The Pure Daisy can turn Sandstone into Aquamarine Shale, which you can dig to obtain Aquamarine.

 With Aquamarine, you'll be able to turn Stone into Marble.

There seems to be something magical about the stars in the night sky. Maybe you could create a special Crafting Table that can utilize the power of starlight for crafting certain items. However, you are going to first need a Wand to focus the starlight in it.
Now that you practically have an infinite supply of Rotten Flesh, you can put it on Drying Racks to turn it into Monster Jerky.
Using the Mana pool, you can essentially turn Seeds into Rice Seeds. Rice can be used as food or making many useful items such as Rice Balls, which can turned into Slime Blocks and then Slime.
You can't possibly memorize everything, so you decided to make a Tome where you write down everything you find out about the stars.
The Luminous Crafting Table is quite limited by the amount of slots it has and starlight it can hold. So you made an Altar with an entire shrine around it in order to increase those things.

With the Luminous Crafting Table you are able to create Obsidian with a lot of Stone. You can then turn that into Rock Crystal Ore with the Pure Daisy. To mine it however, you are going to need an better Pickaxe, so why not also make it out of Obsidian?

By throwing a Sapling into a Mana Pool, it'll turn into a Menril Sapling. Menril trees are much better than regular trees as besides Wood, they provide Menril Berries that can be used as food or for making Menril Torches, and Menril Shards that can later be used for making everything from Integrated Dynamics - a mod used for really complicated automation with reading and writing information.
The Floating Crystal uses starlight to transform blocks linked it it via the Linking Tool. Additionally, it can increase the amount of starlight an Altar linked to it has.

When linking a Floating Crystal to Sand, it turn into Clay. Clay is material that you can shape and dye, so maybe, using starlight, you'be able to turn its many shapes into other, more useful materials.
Light Gray Terracotta, with starlight, can be transmuted into Iron Ore.
Regular Terracotta, with starlight, can be transmuted into Copper Ore.
Light Gray Glazed Terracotta, with starlight, can be transmuted intoTin Ore.
Yellow Terracotta, with starlight, can be transmuted into Gold Ore.
There are Ores that you can make with starlight that don't contain metals.

As you have noticed, when breaking trees you obtain Planks. To obtain Logs, you are going to need an Axe. You can then turn them into 3 Planks by crafting them together with an Axe.

 Similarly, if you don't break Dirt, Gravel or Sand with a Shovel or similar tool, they'll drop 3 of the corresponding type of dust.
Now that you have Iron, you can make a Chisel with which you could far easily make the different types of Marble.

You might be able to use starlight to melt certain items, so you made a special Well. With it, you can melt Leaves into Water, Obsidian into Lava and Aquamarine into Starlight. With those 3 fluids, you could generate Cobblestone, Stone, Sand and Ice.
With the Floating Crystal you can infuse blocks with a limited amount of Starlight. So you made a Starlight Infuser that uses Liquid Starlight to infuse items, when using a Resonating Wand on it.
But the Starlight Crafting Altar simply wasn't enough.
These are all the gem Ore you can make through Starlight Infusion.
When letting Iron Ore infuse with starlight for too long, it turns into Starmetal Ore. You can then turn it into Stardust with a Grindstone.
These are all the metal Ores you can make through Starlight Infusion.
As starlight can transmute items, maybe you could make a wand that uses starlight to replace one type of block with another.

You made an Altar that could use the power of constallations to create items. However, it wasn't limited to an inventory. You can put Spectral Relays around it and put items on them as the recipes need them.

When throwing Stardust and a Rock Crystal in Liquid Starlight, a Celestial Rock Cluster is formed. It seems to slowly grow over time. You put some Starmetal Ore below it and it was able to absorb the starlight in it, using it to grow faster. Maybe, when it's fully grown, it'll drop something interesting.
You can't create enough force with a Hammer to crush down certain items, so you made a machine that uses your own weight to crush them.
Now that you have Quartz, you should make some Quartz Seeds and throw them in Water to grow. You will need them for later use so it's best to have them growing while you're doing something else.

Coal is nice, but you feel like you can make it better. So, you've constructed a multiblock that turns it into Coke Coal and Logs into Charcoal. It also produces Creosote Oil that might be useful later on.
You can't make alloys in a Furnace, but maybe you could construct a small multiblock that can.
Now that you have Emeralds, Coke Coal and an Alloy Kiln, you wanted to see if you could make an alloy out of them, although you knew that most alloys contain metals.

When holding those Dark Gems, you feel weird, like the Blood in your veins is trying to get to it. With them you managed to construct a small device with which you can collect the Blood from mobs you kill. You then, out of curiosity, threw a Dark Gem into a puddle of 5 blocks of Blood to see what happens.
Blood can dry on its own, but you can't quite collect it without it becoming a liquid again. So, you made a Basin in which you could let it dry.
These Dark Gems seem to absorb Blood. Maybe you could use them to infuse other items with Blood.
Since you can infuse items with Blood, maybe you could use it to repair them with it. For that you made a special Chest.

Since Blood mostly contains Iron, you decided to infuse a Block of Iron with Blood. You then sprinkled some Crushed Dark Gems filled with a bit of Blood on top of it. It seemed that instead of collecting the Blood from the Iron Promise Acceptor, they filled it. Maybe you could use this to upgrade the Blood capacity of your Blood Infuser.
Dark Gems are magical and enchantments are magical. Maybe you could make a machine that extracts enchantments and puts them on a Book, one filled with Blood.
Lapis is a magical gem. Maybe you could use it lower the amount of Blood your Blood Infuser uses.
A Promise of Tenacity made out of Gold would allow you to further increase the capacity of your Blood Infuser. It also seems that it allows you to crease some more hellish items.
A Promise of Tenacity made out of Diamonds would allow you to infuse items with souls of the mobs that the Blood belongs to.
Seeing how quick Redstone can transfer a singal, maybe you could infuse it with Blood to have it quickly transfer it.
Some items aren't quite useful in their raw form. You are going to need something that will allow you to grind items down into dust or at least cut them into thinner, longer pieces.
You are able to mix some items in a Cauldron atop a flame.

Sugar gives you energy and Gunpowder contains enough energy to create an explosion. You then mixed them, but the dust you made seemed quite Dull. Maybe infusing it with Blood could turn it into something more interesting.
Having to manually collect Blood isn't fun. Seeing how Dark Gems attract Blood, you thought that maybe a few blocks could collect it in a range.
With Stoneburnt, you've constructed what at first glance looks like a regular Calculator. However, it seems that it doesn't add together numbers, but items.
Now that you can a kinetic energy, you are able make a machine that properly cuts down Logs.
Some items are made up of multiple materials. You are going to need some sort of filter to split up those materials.

Concentrated Hellfire instantly catches on fire, so you made a machine that you can give a Redstone Signal to turn on the Fire. However, it seems that this Fire isn't hot enough for some items to mix or heat up. So you made Bellows with which you can stoke it. They expand when given kinetic energy, so you are going to need to have it constantly turning on and off for the Bellows to work.
You can now make Nether Sludge, which you can smelt to make Nether Bricks.
With some hellish materials, you can now make a Blast Furnace and with it Steel.
Before making multiblocks, are going to have to hit them with a Hammer to make sure everything is working correctly.
Now that you can make Hoppers, you could use them to automatically collect Wood from Bonsai Pots.
You can reinforced your Blast Furnace, allowing you to automate it, and add Blast Furnace Preheaters to it to make it run faster. The Preheaters require RF to function.
Using Marble, you made Grindstone that you'll be able to use for a good chance of Ore doubling.

While breaking Grass, you obtained Hemp Seeds. Unlike other crops, Hemp is too tall to grow on Crop Sticks, so you simply planted it on Farmland. Hemp is a really useful crop as it can be used for making String or Cloth, that both have a lot of uses. Yet, you'll first need a way to turn it into Fibers.

You can't generate an type of power yet, but you can use rotating Axles to make some machines work automatically. They don't seem to be stable when there are more than 3 of them placed in a row, so you are going to need a Gearbox to transfer the energy to other Axles. For the Axles to even to spin though, you are going to need a Windmill. I told you that Creosote Oil could come in handy.
Windmills are nice, but when it rains they break everything. Why don't you instead use the kinetic energy of flowing Water?
Kinetic energy is in other words rotational energy, you could probably make a machine that uses it to rotate blocks and to turn Clay into Crucibles, Vases and Urns.
Using 4 Bricks, you can make a Kiln. When above a Stoked Flame, it allows you to smelt Clay items placed in it, as well as Ores into full Ingots.

When putting Ground Netherrack through a Filtered Hopper, you noticed a strange noise. It sounded like the screams of a Soul. Maybe you could capture it by putting an Urn under it and then use it for making a Steel, infused with it.
You can speed up your Windmill by adding Sails to it.
Using Soulforged Steel, you can make better Gearboxes and Axles, ones that can sustain more kinetic energy.
While kinetic energy works, it's not that ideal. However, it might be possible to turn it into a better type of energy.
Using this new type of Steel you've made, you can make Springs. By adding them to Bellows, you won't need to block their source of kinetic energy for them to work.

With the Soulforged Anvil you can now make a Refined Hacksaw which will allow you to cut Stone and other similar materials into smaller pieces. With these pieces you can make Comparators, Repeators and other blocks used for complex Redstone circuits, as well as an Iron Rod, which you can put on a Sticky Piston to break blocks in front of it.
You can now make a Worktable, which you can use to create many different items, as long as you have the correct Blueprints for them.
You wanted to automate the creation of Wires, Plates, Gears as well as 3x3, 2x2 and uncompressing recipes, so you made a multiblocks machine that uses Molds to do all those things.
A Millstone, Grindstone and a Squeezer aren't good enough for crushing down certain materials. So, you made a machine that can crush down pretty much everything.
By crushing Coal Coke and crafting it with Sand, Gravel and Clay you can make Grout. Grout seems like a perfect material for making a Smeltery with.

Now that you have Grout, you can smelt it into Seared Bricks and with them you can make a basic Smeltery. So that you don't use up too many resources, it's best to make the smallest possible Smeltery and make Seared Stone with it, with which you can then expand it.
The Seared Furnace is a multiblock Furnace that uses Lava to function.
The Tinker Tank is a multiblock tank that can hold different fluids without having them turn into alloys.
The Fuel Input Machine uses Speed Upgrades and Fuel to increase the speed of the Smeltery.
The Stirling Engine uses the heat from a hot fluid in a Seared Tank below it to generate RF.
The Smart Output instantly casts fluids poured into it.
The Carpenter uses RF and fluids to craft certain items.
The Bees produced Combs. You can't directly use them for anything, so you are going to need a machine that can separate them into useful items.
You had some spare Wheat, so you made a machine that moisturizes it and uses the mold to create different natural blocks.
The Still uses RF to turn one fluid into another.

Dilithium seemed like a strange material, so what did you do? You combined it together with another strange material, Purple Slime and Sodium in a Pressurized Reaction Chamber with a large amount of power, because of which you needed Energy Upgrades, and you somehow managed to make an alloy.
The Squeezer uses RF to squeeze items.
With the Mulch you made when squeezing vegetables and fruit, you made Bog Earth. You placed it near Water and it soon turned into Peat.
You have found more compact ways of generating RF.
So you made an Apiary, but you didn't have any Bees. You connected a Floating Crystal to it and now you have Bees. Which though?

To obtain Bees from the Hives you can't use a Pickaxe. You need a more gentle approach. A Scoop will do it. Just to be safe, it's best to use a Smoker on the Hive, so no Bees attack you whle you're breaking it.
From Tropical Bees you can obtain Silk Wisps. Maybe with them you could make an armor set that will protect you from Bee stings.
You needed a way to tell which Bee has which mutations, so you made a Portable Analyzer. You made it use Honey Drops to work as you'll probably have a lot of them soon enough.
The Thermionic Fabricator uses Liquid Glass to create certain items.
Your Blast Furnace wasn't fast and automatable enough for you. Using the Steel you made in it, you upgraded it to be automatable and used RF to heat it up and make it run faster.
Your bronze machines are good, you believed that you can make them faster. So using a Soldering Iron, you added a few Electron Tubes to a Circuit and then added it to the machine you wanted upgraded.

Redstone and Glowstone have a weird glow to them. Perhaps they're radioactive. Knowing that radiation can change DNA, you made a machine that can separate the radioactive particles and one that can apply them to the Bees in order to force mutations. Of course, you can't really control radiation, so your Bees may die.
After a good bit of Bee breeding, you've realized that some Bees don't like breeding in the overworld. So you move to the Nether.
Using Empowered Diamantine Crystals, you were able to create blocks that can wireless interact with other blocks.
Brown Concrete Powder, with starlight, can be transmuted into Dirt.
For dyeing blocks, you are going to need something in which you can put Water and mix it with dyes. So, you made a Cauldron.

Yellow Glazed Terracotta, with starlight, will be transmuted into Pyrite Ore, which drops Sulfur Crystals when crushed. By mixing them with Niter and Coal Dust in a Cauldron, you were able to make Gunpowder. Knowing that Starlight can make things glow, you then put it on a Starlight Infuser.
Just in case the starlight in your chunk wasn't enough, you made a small structure that can redirect the starlight of other chunks into your Floating Crystal and Crafting Altar.
It seems that some items can obsorb mana what thrown into a Mana Pool.
Livingrock by itself cannot absorb mana, however, maybe it can if it's combined with other item. You certainly can't do that manually, but you might be able to create a machine that does that.
It seems that while Iron and Coal do nothing when thrown into a Mana pool, their alloy, Steel, can absorb it.
Diamonds abrob mana, but they can only absorb so much until it escapes back into the Mana Pool. Maybe surrounding one with Livingrock will stop it from escaping.

You already know that you can use starlight for melting, so why not for smelting? All you needed to achieve that was adding a special Lens to a Lens and linking a Crystal to it. Be careful though as the beam between the Lens and the block it's connected to can also burn you.
With Manasteel you can focus mana into Livingrock to make a Rune of Mana.
Putting an Alchemy Catalyst below your Mana Pool will allow you to transmute items using that mana in it.
You can focus mana into Livingrock with materials that represent the different elements to make elemental runes.

With all your Runes you can make a Terrestrial Plate. Throwing Manasteel, a Mana Pearl and a Mana Diamond on it will create Terrasteel. That requires a lot of mana so you are going to need Sparks to quickly transfer it.

You can't simply stay at one place forever to continuously use a Rod. You have better things to do. So you've constructed an Avatar using Livingwood. It uses mana to use Rods in the direction it's facing.
Using elemental Runes, you can make season Runes.
Using the Runes you've already made and Mana Diamonds, you can make sin Runes.
By focusing RF with a Lens, you can use it for transmuting certain items into Crystals.
You can Squeeze Canola to make Canola Oil and with a Still you can then turn it into Refined Canola Oil. You could probably use that for generating RF.
Using the Crystals you made with the Atomic Reconstructor, you are able to make machines that automatically place and destroy blocks.
Those Crystals seem to have so unnatural properties. Maybe you can release their inner energy by combining them with other items. To prove this theory, you've constructed an Empowerer.
Experience isn't quite usable in its default state. Luckly, with Empowered Diamantine Crystals you can make an Experience Solidifier.
With Enori Crystals you are able to construct a machine that automatically collects and places crops.
Now that you have Seared Bricks, you can with a Tool Forge, that allows you to make some more complex tools.

The Liquid Starlight that the Starlight Infuser uses seems to be a bit of a bottleneck. Maybe, using your newest Altar, you could make a Chalice that can hold Liquid Starlight and only the needed amount of it will be used by the Starlight Infuser.

Osmium, besides for not being obtainable as other metals, has some really interesting properties. When given RF, it can infuse certain materials into other materials. Perhaps you could make machines with it.
With the cost of a few Diamonds, you can make a machine that can infuse Stone with 8 of a certain material to make the corresponding Ore.
The Metallurgic Infuser uses a good amount of resources for its infusions. Maybe compressing them could help. For that however, you are going to need yet another machine.
With a Basic Tier Installer, you are able to turn our machines into factories, i.e. give them 3 slots.
Advanced Factories have 5 slots.
Elite Factories have 7 slots.

When mining Redstone Ore, you've noticed that it is sometimes crystallized. Maybe the Osmium in the Combiner has something to do with this? None the less, these Redstone Crystals seem to hold some type of power.

These Redstone Crystals seem to somehow be bound to you. Their, or I guess your power level, seems to increase by exposing them to sunlight or applying force to them. Maybe you can create contraptions that better focus sunlight or force onto them. One of them should be enough to start with.
With the help of some Refractory Wax, you are able to construct a machine that can use the strange power that you've named Grid Power, to create certain items.
You are now able to construct a 1-block generator that uses Coal, Charcoal and their tiny variants.
The Furnace Generator is the base for many, many useful generators.
Now that you have Stoneburnt, you are able to construct machines that can create GP in even more different ways.
You can use a bit of your GP to create a machine that lets you input and output items from many inventories that are connected to it via Transfer Pipes.
By using the items you made with the regular Calculator, you've constructed a Scientific Calculator. With it, you are able to make Redstone Ingots.
To automate your various types of Calculators, you've constructed a special Docking Station.
The Atomic Calculator combines items atom by atom.
The Conductor Mast can collect the power of lightning and redirect it into Fire Diamonds.

Since you can already manipulate atoms, you're starting to believe that using a certain type of Projector, you are able to create a miniaturization field with which you can shrink multiple blocks into one.
In the miniaturisation field, you were able to make rooms in another dimension.
With the miniaturisation field, you are able to create a Machine Frame for some of the best machines out there.
The Magma Crucible will allow you to melt certain items with the cost of RF.
The Induction Smelter allows you to get 3 Ingots per Ore with Cinnabar or Rich Slag. It also allows you to make Hardened Glass and a few alloys.
With a Fluid Transposer, you would be able to infuse certain items with certain fluids.
There are some items that you could make, but would require RF to function. To charge them with said RF, you are going to need an Energizer.

On your mind you had a very demented idea: Using Blood to quickly revive the monsters with their Spirits to then kill them again to obtain their drops. The Spirit would then go back into Box, allowing you to repeat that whole process all over again. For it to work, there would of course need to be enough space inside it for the mob that will momentarily exist to fit. That is just so messed up.
A Redstone Furnace with a Pyrolytic Conversion Augment is essentially a 1-block powered Coke Oven.
The Sequential Fabricator would allow you to autocraft items with power. Although it's very efficient, making a lot of them would be quite expensive.
The Igneous Extruder uses RF, Water and Lava to generate the different variants of Stone, Cobblestone and Obsidian.
The Glacial Precipitator uses RF and Water to generate Snow and Ice.
Now that you can make Coils and you can power items, you are able to make and use Jetpacks.
No Description
No Description
You are able to turn your Flux-Infused Chestplate into a Jetplate.
No Description
The Hardened Upgrade Kit will allow you to turn your TE machines into their Hardened variants. Seeing how expensive they are, upgrading them would probably be more efficient than making new ones.
The Reinforced Upgrade Kit will allow you to turn your TE machines into their Reinforced variants.
The Signalum Upgrade Kit will allow you to turn your TE machines into their Signalum Variants.
The Resonant Upgrade Kit will allow you to turn your TE machines into their Resonant Variants.
By exploding TNT near Iron, 80 percent of in will be turned into Compressed Iron.
You can use Compressed Iron to create a machine that uses fuel to generate pressure.
Some items would require pressure to work, so you should make something to charge them with.
You are able to construct a chamber that is at least a 3x3x3 with which you can pressurize items.
Using pressure, you might be able to separate heat and transfer it with Compressed Iron Blocks.
With Compressed Iron, you are able to construct a machine that uses heat to refine Oil.
Tectonic Petrotheum has properties similar to those of Oil. Maybe you could somehow turn it into Oil.
You might be able to construct a machine that uses pressure and heat to turn LPG into Molten Plastic.
Sice you've already made Molten Plastic, it shouldn't be too difficult to turn it into regular Plastic.
With Plastic, you are able to construct a Tablet that, using pressure, somehow connects you to Villagers.
You could use pressure to move yourself upwards.
Fluxed Electrum seems to be a really strong metal, as surprising as it may be with Electrum being really weak. Armor made from it, as long as it's charged, should be quite powerful.
Using some Pressure and bombarding an Empty PCB with UV radiation, you should be able to increase the chance that it will properly be etched.
By throwing an Empty PCB, that was exposed to UV radiation, in Etching Acid, it will be turned into an Unassembled PCB.
It seems that it's quite easy and hard to alloy Osmium. You see, unlike other metals, you need to compress another material with it in order to alloy it.
Using an assembly line, you are able to make Advanced Pressure Tubes. With them, you can construct machines that can switch between RF and pressure.
With Printed Circuit Boards, you are able to create a whole assembly line.

You might be able to create a special Lens that, when put on the Atomic Reconstructor, will make it turn Stone and Netherrack in front of it into Ore. It won't be cheap and it won't be fast, but having multiple of them would be efficient.
Using Terrasteel, you might be able to construct a portal to another dimension. However, it won't be strong enough for you to pass through it.
The Compactor allows you to easily make Plates, compress items and, when given the right Augment, make Gears.
With Plastic Sheets, you can create a machine that perfectly kill mobs. Maybe too perfectly.

Many things in this world seem to contain some type of essence, however, when you collect it, it isn't as useful. Some you believe that you could make one of two machines that collect it in its raw form: a Crusher that collects it from mobs or a Furnace that collects it from smelted items.
So you placed some Pink Slime on the ground to see what it will do and it seems to come to life. When killing it, it might drop something useful.
This Pink Slime seems to somehow be linked to the void. Maybe you could construct a machine that uses it to collect Ores from the void, ones that you can't make with starlight.
By pouring Essence onto Mirion, you would be able to make an alloy made out of almost pure magic.

Using the 3rd Promise of Tenacity, you were able to turn Skulls into Wither Skeleton Skulls. With them, you could create a monster that has been mentioned in many legends: The Wither. Once you collect its Star, it shouldn't be too difficult to recreate it.
Using the Induction Smelter, you can also refined Iron with Consecrated Hellfire.
Since you already have most things running on power, why not also have your allloying powered?
Rubies and similar gems contain a large mix of chemicals. Maybe you could make a machine to separate them with with RF.
Sometimes you want chemical reactions to happen, but naturally they can't. Luckly, you can now make a machine that makes some chemical reactions possible.
Some everyday things can be separatedd into more basic components by spinning them quickly. To achieve that you are going to need a machine.
With the Industrial Centrifuge, you've managed to extract a special type of Oil from Soulsand. To get anything useful out of this one however, you are going to need to distill it.
It seems that you can't so easily compress Iridium Alloy to make Plates. What if you were to implode it though?
There are somethings that are to tough for you to bend and some that you can't bend as well manually. Luckly, you can make a machine that does all the bending for you.
You've often found yourself having a lot of useless items. Why not turn them into Scrap? You might then get something useful from it.

You've often imagined a time of Clay that you could shape into any material. Now that you have Chrome, that might not be far from possible. Just throw in some scrap and a few million RF and you could make UU-Matter.
Helium isn't so hard to make. Maybe hitting a lot of Helium atoms into each other could turn them into a type of Plasma. It would probably be a great source of RF.

You imagine an alloy that combines the attributes of Steel and Tungsten: Tungstensteel. To make it however, you'd have to reach a pretty high temperature. An Industrial Blast Furnace filled with Lava should be able to reach said temperature. You'd probably also need a way to cool it after you make it.
Tungstensteel, which you now have, should be durable enough to contain Heliumplasma. You now make a generator that utilizes the heat of said Heliumplasma.
With UU-Matter you are able to create a nuclear material known as Yellorium. With it, you could power an extreme reactor.

As the generators are working, they slowly create a byproduct, Cyanite. Colling that with Water creates Blutonium. But that's not all. Combining that with Enderium and Blaze Rods can then create Ludicrite.

When under a large amount of pressure, Blazing Pyrotheum collects the power around it and crystallizes. With a special machine, you should be able to get the energy out of it in it's raw state, Ember.
To move this energy, you are going to need some mystical objects. To guide it through them, however, you are going to need a Hammer, one of a true tinkerer.
Water contains a really small amount of Salt. Maybe you could make a machine that evporates it and leaves over some Brine.
To get Salt, all you need to do is crystallize the Brine.

So you had a weird thought for a moment: "What if everything has a Circuit in it". So you built a machine, put a piece of Cobblestone in it and wouldn't you know it, it had a Circuit in it! It was damaged, but it was there. After a it of experimenting, you determined that only certain blocks contain Circuits.
Damaged Circuits can't really be used for anything, so yu made a machine to fix them up.

So you wanted to check the stability of the Circuits before using it. As always, you made a machine for it. However, you found that one of the Circuits had an item it in. So blocks have Circuits in them, that can have items in them. This is quite a strange world.
Since Ember is a type of energy, you decided to try to use it for one of the most basic tasks that use heat: alloying.

Using the energ, that is Ember, you've managed to create an alloy you couldn't make in any other machine, Dawnstone. However, as it is infused with Ember, it doesn't seem to cool down by itself. So what if you instead were to Stamp it. Then, maybe all of it's items we clump up in a way that they'll stop moving and it will become a solid.
As Ember is a type of energy, maybe if you focus it, using Dawnstone, you'd be able to kill mobs with it.

After all, Ember is a mystical type of energy, so maybe you could use it for doing some magic with it. So, you made a Tablet on which you can put items and a few Pedestals that you can fill up with Ash. You gave it Ember via a Receptor and nothing happened. Then you tried marking the Pedestals with Aspecti and giving it focused Ember. It worked, but everything turned into Alchemical Waste. Hope is not lost however, this Waste seems to indicate how many Ash Piles you were away from succeeding.
Emitters and Receptor work, but they aren't the best. Now that you have Dawnstone and alchemy, you could probably upgrade them.

The Mixer Centrifuge seems to be limited by something, so, using alchemy, you've made a machine that enhances it when put on the side of its upper block. It allows you to combine alchemy with alloying, using Ash Piles to mix metals.
To start making space gear, you are going to need to make Silicon. In order to make it, you are going to need an Electric Blast Furnace.
Since you can't quite easily remember everything you need for going to space, you've made a device that does that for you.
Although you've already separated Water before, it's easier to store Oxygen and Hydrogen  as a liquids, so you've made an Electrolyzer that separates them as liquids.
Silicon can't be made into a Wafer, when it's an Ingot. However, to turn it into a Boule, you are going to have to crystallize it.
To survive in Space, you are going to need Oxygen stored in a Pressure Tank. Although you already have a Rolling Machine, it's not big enough to make the Pressure Tank.
To survive in space, youare going to need a Space Suit. You can add Pressure Tanks to it using a Suit Workbench and you can fill them up by standing on a Charge Pad.
When working with Rockets, Silicon Wafers need to be perfectly cut. Sadly, you can't do that, but you can make a machine that does.
As you've probably already learned, Circuits aren't simple to make. You are going to need a machine that is precise.
You can now make a special Still that refines Oil into Refined Oil.
Your current Chemical Reactor can only combine 2 fluids. However, you can now make a bigger and better one that can combine more fluids. You are going to need it for making Rocket Fuel.
Usually, Water and Heavy Water are mixed together. By adding a filted to a Pump, you could probably separate them.
Some fluids can be separated with a specific amount of RF. So, you've made a machine out of Osmium, that you hope will achieve that.
Osmium seems to be able to turns gases into liquids and vise versa. Maybe you could make a machine that can switch between the two.

To make High Density Polyethyline, you are first going to need Ethyline. Ethyline is a byproduct of pressurizing Water and Hydrogen together with Bio Fuel, which you can make by crushing down plants. Then you pressurize the Ethyline with the Substrate you made when making Ethyline.
With HDPE, you can make a machine that can focus neutrons onto Lithium to make Tritium.
One of the many interesting properties of Osmium is that it can force certain gases to react. You can make a machine for this!

To build a Rocket, you are going to need a Launch Pad with the length and width of your Rocket, connected to a Structure Tower at least one block taller than your Rocket. The Rocket can have just about anything, but it must have a Guidance Computer with a Planet ID Chip, a Seat and a few Liquid Fueled Engines and Liquid Fuel Tanks.
Now you have everything needed for going to the Moon. Just fuel up, select your destination and lift off! On the Moon, you can find your regular Ores, but you'll most importantly find Dilithium.

Remember those Quartz Seeds? They've grown into Pure Quartz, which you can infuse with Diamonds in the Metallurgic Infuser to make Pure Certus Quartz. You can turn 8 of them into a block and then you craft it into regular Certus Quartz.

Now that you have Machine Frames, you can make a machine to change your Certus Quartz with. Once charged, it seems to gravitate towards Redstone and Quartz. You wonder what would happen if you were to throw them together. Just in case of explosions, let's do it in Water.
It seems that Lumium allows helps plants grow faster. You wonder whether you could make a machine that grows plants faster and whether or not it would help the crystal Seeds grow faster.
In order to manipulate matter, you are going to need special Processors that have been made with the power of Fluix Crystals. So you've made an Inscriber.
This is the core of you Material Energy system. However, as advanced as the technology might be, it's limited to 32 channels and 1 cannot be touching 4 other Controller blocks.
To actually store matter as energy you are going to need Disks. However, to connect them to your system, you are going to need a Drive.
Since you can already turn matter into energy, what's stopping you from making a Singularity? All you need is a Matter Condenser and a 64k Storage Component to store the extra energy on.
You can now make a Calculator with which you can turn Wood into Obsidian and Gold Ingots into Diamonds!
With the Chorus Fruit, that you can now make, you can make a Cake that takes you to a whole new dimension: The End.
In the End, you've found Ore filled with the essence of Dragons. Using Ember, you managed to focus it into Manyullyn to make Draconium Ingots.
Although you've stored items as energy, you can't really access them. To actually access them, you are going to need a special Monitor that can convert the energy back into items.

Right now, you can use your ME system for storing and crafting stuff, but that doesn't make it much different from the Indexer. However, seeing how easily Fluix Crystals can turn matter into energy and vise versa, if were to give them specific Patterns, you could use them for automating most things.
With this alloy, you were able to make a Frame for machines that can detect and manipulate atoms in an area.

Although the Sequential Fabricator works quite fast, it can only do a recipe at a time, which doesn't make it too efficient. However, you can now make a machine that does do multiple recipes at a time and isn't quite as expensive if you have everything automated.
You are now able to create machine that, when given a pattern and the corresponding blocks, can replicate a build, atom by atom.
You now have the technology that would allow you to teleport you, atom by atom, to a specific location.
It seems that, similarly to Black Quartz, Draconium uses RF to combine items. However, the items that you can make it with are simply over-powered.
For starters, you can quite quickly upgrade the entire setup using it.

It seems that those Crystals in the End healed the Dragon. Maybe you could use them to revive it.


 The new Dragon doesn't seems to drop an Egg however. Maybe you could make something that will focus the energy of the End onto the Dragon, that will force it to drop an Egg.
Using Dragon Hearts, you are now able to awaken the true power of Draconium.
Using Awakened Draconium, you can now make gear that will, in a way give you the power of a Dragon. Gear that is more upgradeable and customizable than any other.

So you decided to explore the End. For a while it seemed like there are only islands upon islands, but then you found a City. It was... interesting. However, after travelling 10k blocks away from the main island, you found a Dragon, one much stronger than the Ender Dragon. You wanted to fight it, but you also wanted to gear up first.

 Once you killed it, nothing happened. Seeing how big its island was, you decided to check if there was anything in it. To your surprise, there was a massive crystal in it. So you broke it. The whole place quickly started collapsing, hence you decided to call it a Chaos Crystal.
So you could now access your network, but it was only from one point. So you wanted to make it wireless. Before you could do that, you needed a way to authorise yourself.

Seeing that those Chaos Crystals can keep an entire island from collapsing, you wondered what you could make with a Core made from them. Maybe a new dimension?

 And so you did that, you created your custom dimension. However, after a bit of exploration, you found some strange structures and a strange Ore that you have never even heard of before.
With these strange Crystals, you were able to make what you always dreamt of: a machine that can duplicate items. It might use a lot of power, but it does its job.

This is it, you beat the pack! Now you can gladly say that you beat Crimson Skies. I'm guessing you expected something more, like overpowered gear. That however, isn't the case. As a wise man once said: "It's not about the destination, it's about the journey". And this my friend is the end your journey. I hope that you enjoyed and learned something new.

 An until next time, take care.

 -Pixel

To make certain items, you need to use tools or fluids during the crafting process. That you can't do with a regular old Crafting Table.

 You left a Crafting Table next to a Pure Daisy by mistake. When you came back to it, it had turned into Basic Worktable. You couldn't quite do anything with it, but maybe with starlight you can turn it into what you need.

You made a special Lens that could break the blocks it's connected to. You can't quite turn it on and off, so all you could really do with it is automating your Cobblestone generator, unless you have other ideas.
You used the Resonating Crystal to make a machine that can use tools as you can.
For easily harvesting Hemp and shearing, you made a Kama.
For chopping down trees, digging Dirt and similar materials, tilling soil and potentially killing monsters, you made a Mattock.
Once you made your Industrial Blast Furnace, you mixed the Tar you had left from making Naphta, with Coke Coal, and made Graphite.
You cooked up the Slime you previously made with Rice Balls, crystallizing it in the process. It slightly looks like an Emerald, so maybe, with the Starlight Infuser, you could turn it into one.
Between the crops you had, you placed 2 sets of Crop Sticks, on top of each other. You started watering them and after a while, you managed to obtain Carrots, Sugar Canes, Pumpkins and Melons.
Using the metal you got through the portal, you made a new catalyst, one that would allow your Mana Pool to recreate items using mana.
You moved your cross-breeding on Grass. You obtained some Flowers that you had never seen before. Perhaps the Grass on your island has magical properties.

Rock Crystals, when exposed to starlight, seem to bind to the type of block they're touching. So, you made Rock Crystal tools and infused them with starlight. Maybe you could get them to break a type of block in an area (by holding shift while breaking).

For the Cauldon to work, you need a flame below it, however, on top of most blocks it just randomly extinguishes or burns away the block. Using starlight, you were able to turn Slime into somewhat Liquid Magma. A flame on top of it seems to last forever.

Using the Iridescent Altar, you were able to create Constellation Papers. Using a Telescope, you managed to find them and draw them in the sky. You then wondered what they meant, what power they held. You had a crazy idea; what if you attuned yourself to one of them. And so you made a new Altar. Following the Papers, you placed down Spectral Relays on the Sooty Marble, in the place of the stars, and then jumped in it.

Osmium seems to be obtainable in 2 ways:
-With a perk of Aevitas that can turn nearby Stone into the Ore
-With a perk of Mineralis that can have the Ore drop when breaking Stone.
 Seeing how only 2 Constellations allow you to obtain it, there must be something special about it.

The area of effect perks are nice, but you can't sit at one place forever. So, instead of you bieng there, maybe you could have a Rock Crystal give out the effect for you. However, it isn't that simple. You are going to need a Pedestal to place it on. Yet, that has its ups. You can have an Anchor 3 blocks above it linked to another one to move the effect to it. You can also link a Floating Crystal to the Pedestal and place Lenses where required to enhance the effect.
Using the Rune of Mana, you were able to create a Rose that can collect experience from the ground. This would be useful for a mob farm.
Slime is a viscous fluid, so if you face it in a specific direction, you might have mobs spawn on it and then move in the corresponding direction.
Some Bees can only survive in certain conditions. So, you made a machine that can hopefully satisfy the needs of every Bee.

Seeing that these Dark Gems are somehow attracted towards you Blood, perhaps they are also attracted to spirits. So, you made a ring out of them. However, if this Ring does work as you intend it to, you will probably want a way to capture it for safe keeping. A Box made out of these Dark Gems should work.

By adding Nether Stars and Chorus Fruit to your Ring of Vengeance, you managed to create an item with which you can kill a Vengeance Spirit. Killing something twice!? That's probably the most messed up thing you've done so far. Although, I guess its Essence could come in handy.
...it's still messed up though.
Everything has a beginning. This is the beginning of this pack.
The power of starlight is much greater than you thought. Don't underestimate it.
You can't solve every problem by being a nice guy.
All this manual work for just a few Nuggets per Ore isn't fun. It's time to change that.
They say that the more friends you have the happier you'll be. Bees can bee friends, right?

While Starlight can be used for transmuting items, it's a weak type of magic. You have already seen the magical properties of mana, so you question what else you can do with it. Maybe power is also hiding secrets.
You've made a good amount of machines, so you wonder what else you could add to them.
You are now able to construct machines that take up only one block, but are really powerful.
You are now able to construct machines with which you can construct pressure.
Now that you can refine Iron, you might be able to create some new machines.

You've realized that there is some type of mystical energy in this land. I mean, you're on a floating platform in the void, it was a bit obvious. Anyways, you're now trying to use this energy for your own deeds.
The Moon - it's the only thing in the sky that isn't magical, so you decide to travel to it.
You once heard a few scientists say E=mc^2. You finally understood what it means. But if that is so, what have you been doing this entire time?
